        "collapsible_row_xHmxih": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Warranty Policy",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<h1><strong>Zinara Warranty Policy</strong></h1><p>At Zinara, we take pride in the exceptional craftsmanship and quality of our jewellery. Every product is thoughtfully designed and meticulously crafted - and we stand behind it.<br/> That’s why all Zinara jewellery comes with a <strong>statutory 12-month warranty</strong>, giving you peace of mind with every purchase.</p><p>If you experience any issue covered under warranty, simply write to us at <strong>help@zinara.in</strong>, and our team will guide you through the process.</p><h1><strong>What the Warranty Covers</strong></h1><p>Our 12-month warranty covers <strong>manufacturing defects and material defects</strong> arising from normal use of the product.</p><p>If your jewellery is found to have a defect during this period, Zinara will, at its discretion:</p><ul><li>Repair the item<br/><br/></li><li>Replace it with an identical piece (if available)<br/><br/></li><li>Substitute it with a piece of comparable value<br/><br/></li></ul><p>Warranty coverage applies <strong>only after verification</strong> by the Zinara Quality Team and may vary by region and market.</p><p><strong>Please note:<br/></strong>Coverage includes only defects that Zinara determines are <em>not</em> the result of accident, misuse, negligence, wear and tear, modification, or attempted repair outside of Zinara.</p><h1><strong>What the Warranty Does Not Cover</strong></h1><p>To maintain transparency and service quality, the following are <strong>not covered</strong> under Zinara’s warranty:</p><h3><strong>1. Purchases from Unauthorized Sellers</strong></h3><p>Products bought from resellers, third-party vendors, or unauthorized platforms are not eligible. Please contact the original seller for assistance.</p><h3><strong>2. Unauthorized Repairs or Modifications</strong></h3><p>Any repairs, stone resetting, resizing, polishing, or modifications done by an outside jeweller will void the warranty.</p><p>This includes:</p><ul><li>Engraving<br/><br/></li><li>Altering the design<br/><br/></li><li>Adding or removing elements<br/><br/></li><li>Attempted repairs of any kind<br/><br/></li></ul><h3><strong>3. Loss, Wear & Tear, or Misuse</strong></h3><p>The warranty does not cover:</p><ul><li>Lost items<br/><br/></li><li>Damage caused by improper use or storage<br/><br/></li><li>Everyday wear and tear (scratches, fading, dents, etc.)<br/><br/></li><li>Accidental damage or negligence<br/><br/></li></ul><h3><strong>4. Promotional or Complimentary Items</strong></h3><p>Free gifts, promotional products, or giveaway items may not carry warranty unless specifically stated.</p><h1><strong>Warranty Claim Process</strong></h1><p>To initiate a claim:</p><ol><li><strong>Write to us</strong> at <strong>help@zinara.in</strong> with your concern<br/><br/></li><li>Provide your <strong>order ID / proof of purchase</strong>, and <strong>certificate of authenticity</strong> (if applicable)<br/><br/></li><li>Our team will assess your case and may request that you <strong>return the item</strong> for inspection<br/><br/></li></ol><p>All defective items must be sent via post or courier for a thorough evaluation.</p><p>Warranty inspections and approved repairs/replacements are offered <strong>free of charge</strong>.</p><h1><strong>Required Documentation</strong></h1><p>To validate your warranty claim, please retain:</p><ul><li>Original invoice or order confirmation<br/><br/></li><li>Gift receipt (if applicable)<br/><br/></li><li>Certificate of authenticity/ Diamond certificate for eligible products</li></ul><p>These documents serve as proof of purchase and entitlement to warranty service.</p><h1><strong>Important Notes</strong></h1><ul><li>Zinara may update or amend these warranty terms at any time, with prospective effect.<br/><br/></li><li>This warranty operates <strong>in addition to your statutory rights</strong>, not in place of them.<br/><br/></li></ul><p>We are committed to offering you a seamless and reassuring experience.<br/>If you have questions or need help, our team is always here to assist at <strong>help@zinara.in</strong>.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_yyQ3U6": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Shipping Policy",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>We offer FREE shipping within India, which includes GST in MRP. Shipping time is 24 – 48 hrs for ‘Available in Stock’ items and 24-30 business days for “Make to order” items. After your item has been packaged, it will be shipped and delivered free through an insured courier. We urge all customers to inspect the package for any damage or tamper before receiving or signing for receipt. All customers will receive a personalized confirmation email with tracking information once the order is received and shipped. If an item is sold out, our account executives will notify you promptly.</p><p><br/>Every ZINARA jewellery package is carefully wrapped to ensure its safety during delivery. All your items are presented in a ZINARA box along with the necessary certificates.<br/><br/>NOTE : We retain the right to adjust this shipping policy as needed, hence we encourage you to check it regularly. Any modifications or clarifications will be implemented immediately upon being posted on the website.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_xd978X": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Cancellation Policy",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p><strong>Cancellation By Zinara</strong>:</p><p>There may be certain orders that Zinara cannot accept, and therefore, we reserve the right, at our sole discretion, to refuse or cancel any order. Some reasons may include limitation on quantity available for purchase; errors in pricing or product information or certain issues identified by our fraud avoidance department or any other issue which Zinara identifies for not accepting the order. We also reserve the right to ask for additional information for accepting orders in certain cases. We will notify you in case your order has been cancelled fully or partially or if any additional information is required to accept your order.</p><p><strong>Cancellation by Customer</strong>:</p><p>Once an order is placed, it can only be cancelled before it is shipped from our warehouse. Registered customers can always check the status of their order from the Track Order option available at<a href=\"http://www.zinara.in/\">www.zinara.in</a>. Once the cancellation request is received, we will initiate the process of refunding the amount to your account via the same payment mode that you had used to make the transaction or through cheque (amount would be refunded through cheque, only in cases where the debit/credit card used by customer while placing the order is not in use). Once the refund process is initiated, you will receive the refund amount directly in your account within 7-15 business days or through cheque, which can take upto 30 days for delivery.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_488rGf": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Privacy Policy",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>Privacy Policy</p><p>Introduction</p><p>Welcome to ZINARA, your trusted destination for lab-grown diamond jewellery. We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring the security of your personal information. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, disclose, and protect your information when you visit our website and purchase our products.</p><ol><li>Information We Collect</li></ol><p>We collect various types of information to provide and improve our services, including:</p><p><strong>Personal Information: Name, email address, phone number, billing and shipping address, payment information, and other details necessary for processing your orders.</strong></p><p><strong>Usage Data: Information about how you use our website, such as your IP address, browser type, operating system, and browsing behavior.</strong></p><p><strong>Cookies and Tracking Technologies: We use cookies and similar technologies to enhance your experience on our website, analyze site traffic, and understand user preferences.</strong></p><ol><li>How We Use Your Information</li></ol><p>We use your information for the following purposes:</p><p><strong>Order Processing: To process and fulfill your orders, including sending order confirmations, shipping notifications, and customer support.</strong></p><p><strong>Personalization: To personalize your shopping experience and recommend products that may interest you.</strong></p><p><strong>Communication: To send you promotional offers, newsletters, and updates about our products and services. You can opt-out of marketing communications at any time.</strong></p><p><strong>Improvement: To analyze website usage and improve our services, website functionality, and user experience.</strong></p><p><strong>Legal Compliance: To comply with legal obligations and protect our rights and interests.</strong></p><ol><li>Disclosure of Your Information</li></ol><p>We may share your information with third parties under the following circumstances:</p><p><strong>Service Providers: We may share your information with trusted service providers who assist us in operating our website, processing payments, and delivering orders.</strong></p><p><strong>Legal Requirements: We may disclose your information if required by law or in response to valid requests by public authorities.</strong></p><p><strong>Business Transfers: In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of all or a portion of our assets, your information may be transferred as part of the transaction.</strong></p><ol><li>Security of Your Information</li></ol><p>We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p><ol><li>Your Rights</li></ol><p>You have the following rights regarding your personal information:</p><p><strong>Access: You can request access to the personal information we hold about you.</strong></p><p><strong>Correction: You can request that we correct any inaccurate or incomplete information.</strong></p><p><strong>Deletion: You can request that we delete your personal information, subject to certain legal obligations.</strong></p><p><strong>Opt-Out: You can opt-out of receiving marketing communications from us.</strong></p><p>To exercise your rights, please contact us at <strong>admin@zinara.in</strong></p><ol><li>Cookies and Tracking Technologies</li></ol><p>We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to enhance your browsing experience, analyze website traffic, and understand user behavior. You can manage your cookie preferences through your browser settings.</p><ol><li>Third-Party Links</li></ol><p>Our website may contain links to third-party websites. We are not responsible for the privacy practices or content of these websites. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of any third-party sites you visit.</p><ol><li>Changes to This Privacy Policy</li></ol><p>We reserve the right to modify this Privacy Policy at any time. Changes will take effect immediately upon posting on our website. If we make significant changes, we will notify you here to ensure you are aware of the updates.</p><ol><li>Contact Us</li></ol><p>If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at: <strong>admin@zinara.in</strong><br/><br/></p><p>Thank you for trusting ZINARA with your lab-grown diamond jewellery needs. We are committed to safeguarding your privacy and providing you with an exceptional shopping experience.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        }
